    <stitle>STEERING COLUMN ASSEMBLY, TILT/TELESCOPING - MAINTENANCE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>MAINTENANCE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="pm" graphiccount="0">
            <title>END YOKE PINCH BOLTS</title>
            <para>The pinch bolts and nuts on the lower steering column end yokes should be checked for tightness
                annually or every 50,000 miles (80,000 kilometers), whichever comes first. Visually inspect that the
                plastic collar has been sheared off.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
